[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, I don\'t generally focus on a single product in a video unless it is a bit special. And the new Loop Gear SK05 Pro2 flashlight or torch is because it has just moved into my number one spot for a handheld flashlight. Edging out my'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'previous favorite, the Nycore EDC 37. So, let\'s see what makes this so good. And just to be clear, this video is not sponsored. Now, Loop Gear is a relatively new maker, having only been'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'around since 2022, and they are getting a name for great design, quality, and innovation. And the new SK05 Pro 2 is an upgrade to the SK05 Pro, which I'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reviewed just over a year ago and really liked. But the new Pro Two here is a significant step up with better handling and increased power in all modes alongside some other tweaks that combine'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to make all the difference. It appears almost identical to the original, which is no bad thing as I really like the look, size, and shape of this light, which incorporates lots of nice design'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'details. It\'s made from aluminium and it\'s available in a black anodized finish, the one I have here, and also a super tough MAO finish, which is available in white and also in gray. And'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'as we\'ve come to expect from Loop Gear, the overall quality is excellent. Now, the top-mounted rotary switch here with a central push button remains from the original. Again, that\'s good as this'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really simplifies the operation, but it\'s been noticeably improved. It\'s smoother, more clicky, and has a lot less friction than the original and can now be easily operated with the thumb,'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'helped by this grippy nurlet. And it seems like a small thing, but it actually makes a big difference in use. The rotary switch has four positions. A lock, which is always great to see, and'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from there you switch to flood, which uses this triple lens array. And then you switch to beam with this deep reflector for long range. And then you switch to the sidelight here, which I\'ll come back to. All the light outputs with'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the new version have been increased. The flood now has a maximum turbo output of 3,800 lumens, up from 3,60. And the spotlight now has a maximum'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'output of 2 1/2,000 lumens, double the original, 1300, giving the light an impressive 410 m range. And one of the best features of this light is that you'

[02:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can easily switch between spot and flood using the rotary switch. And you can even have different light levels for each. So you might be walking along with the flood light at a medium light level.'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And then you can instantly switch to the beam, say at a high light level to illuminate something in the distance, and then quickly go back again to the flood light. And to change the light level, you simply press and hold the center button to step through low,'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'medium, and high. And if you need more light, a double press takes you to a turbo for up to a 30-second burst, and another double press takes you back again. This separate dedicated beam and'

[03:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'flood lens arrangement is generally more effective than a single lens trying to do both. You can though bring on both at the same time at the maximum turbo output to create a very bright combined'

[03:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'flood and beam with a 5,000 lumen output for relatively short bursts. And a triple click will bring on a super bright combined lens strobe which can'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'also be switched to a flashing SOS pattern. Another really welcome step up for the version two is the improved sidelight. And this now incorporates an additional 38 high CRI or color corrected white LEDs alongside the 22'

[03:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'color RGB LEDs from the original. And this increases the white light output from one lumen we saw on the original, which was not that useful, to an'

[03:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'impressive 120 lumens with the Pro 2, which is a huge improvement. And this creates a very useful bright diffused color accurate light with four light levels. As with the original, there are five'

[04:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'flashing and phasing sidelight options which you step through with a double click. And you can choose from seven color options with a press and hold. These I still find a bit novelty and I would prefer just red as it means of'

[04:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'being seen at night along with the white light which would make for easier operation. However, those who do want different light colors to choose from won\'t be disappointed. There is also the sidelight equivalent of a strobe, which'

[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like the main light, requires a triple press, and that results in this flashing blue and red effect. Now, I\'m not really a fan of this light pattern because in the UK, this could be seen as imitating the police or emergency services, which'

[04:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'might not go down too well. However, in an emergency situation, say to warn motorists at night of an impending danger, it is, I have to say, very bright and very effective. The light incorporates two 18 650 batteries with a'

[05:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'combined 8,000 mAh capacity, and that gives some great run times. For example, the low setting, which is 40 lumens for the spot and 50 for the flood, which is bright enough to light your way home in'

[05:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the dark, is good, we are told, for 48 hours on a single charge. It is worth noting that there is no one lu moonlight option on the main lights. However, the sidelight does have a 1 L option along'

[05:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with 1040 and that 120 L output again with some impressive run times. The batteries are replaceable via a lockable'

[05:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hatch at the rear of the light. And you might notice that the batteries both face the same way in the light, which points to them being connected in parallel. And that means if one battery is removed, the light still works as'

[05:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'normal, albeit with reduced run times. The light is charged via a USBC port, which on the Pro 2 now has a metal flap, replacing the original rubber one. And this can be fast charged at up to 22 W.'

[06:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And very usefully, the USBC port is two-way, meaning the light can also double up as a power bank to charge your other devices also at up to 22 watts. So, if you carry a flashlight and a'

[06:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'power bank in case they might be needed, this could do the job of both, saving weight and space. Add to that a new lanyard attachment point, a magnetic base, a battery level indicator using'

[06:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the sidebar LEDs, a great belt or pocket clip, plus an IP68 rating, meaning this thing can cope with all the elements, including full submersion in water. and it\'s really hard to know what more you'

[06:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'could want. In a practical sense, the light fits perfectly into the hand. The use of the 18650 batteries here, I think, are a good choice, keeping the light relatively compact. And also, when it comes to handling, the rotary switch'

[07:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and push buttons fall precisely where the thumb sits, so you can always easily find the controls in the dark. My favorite handheld flashlight up until now has been the Nightcore EDC37. It\'s a'

[07:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'great light with the same capacity as the SK05 in a slightly smaller form factor and that is achieved by making the batteries non-replaceable. So, it is a compromise. It also has the excellent'

[07:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'OLED power and duration display which it has to be said is a real asset. It has two smaller shallower reflectors with multiledd arrays which gives a mix of beam and flood so you don\'t get to'

[07:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'choose one over the other at the main light levels. The maximum range in what Nightcore call search mode is though still impressive at a quoted 420 meters at 3,000 lumens. So around the same as'

[07:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the SK05, albeit with a bit more light spill. And the EDC37 also has a bonkers bright 8,000 lumen flood light called Lumen Shield, but that\'s for short'

[08:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '10-second bursts only. The SK05 does though hold its own with that combined spot and flood 5,000 lumen output which is not quite as bright, but it can maintain the output for closer to 30'

[08:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'seconds which is arguably more useful. The SK05 also has that switchable beam and flood, the fourle bright white sidelight, and the various color options which can also be used as a warning'

[08:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'light. We also have that genuinely useful power bank feature along with a magnetic tail cap which also allows for self-standing. And those replaceable 18650 batteries don\'t just potentially prolong the life of the light when the'

[08:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'batteries eventually start to degrade, but it also means that if you run low on power, you can simply swap them out for a fully charged set and keep going. And even if you just have one available, it will still work as we have seen. So,'

[08:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'comparing the SK05 Pro 2 and the EDC37 side by side, the SK05, I believe, offers more overall practical utility, which is why it moves into my number one'

[09:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'spot for a handheld torch or flashlight. And let\'s not forget the price. The SK05 lists at £150 or $160. However, I\'ve seen some great offers'

[09:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'online at the time of filming with at least 20% off, which I think is great value considering what you\'re getting. So, there you have it. My new favorite'

[09:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'torch or flashlight for now at least. Let me know in the comments what you think and if you think there is something better out there that I might have missed. But for now, thank you as always for watching and I hope you can'

[09:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'join me for the next'
